Heineken Slumps in Amsterdam After Forecasting Stagnant Full-Year Profit

-- B y   M a r t i j n   v a n   d e r   S t a r r e
-- 
2011-08-24T07:02:57Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-24/heineken-slumps-after-saying-full-year-profit-likely-to-be-similar-to-2010.html
Heineken NV (HEIA)  fell in Amsterdam
trading after the world’s third-largest brewer by volume said
full-year profit is unlikely to grow after reporting first-half
earnings that missed estimates.  Heineken declined 13 percent to 31.61 euros as of 9:02 a.m.
local time.  So-called organic net income for 2011 will be “broadly in
line” with last year’s 1.45 billion euros ($2.1 billion), the
Amsterdam-based company said today in a statement. Analysts
estimated adjusted profit for the year of 1.68 billion euros,
according to the average of 23 estimates compiled by Bloomberg.  First-half earnings before interest and tax rose to 1.26
billion euros, excluding some items, from 1.14 billion euros a
year earlier, the company said. The median estimate of five
analysts surveyed by Bloomberg was 1.37 billion euros.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Martijn van der Starre at 
 vanderstarre@bloomberg.net  